byline.contributor: Jeffrey Gettleman contributed reporting from Nairobi, Kenya.

abstract: Islamic militant group Shabab claims responsibility for two suicide bombings in Baidoa, Somalia, near outdoor cafe frequented by government workers; blasts killed at least 20 people and injured 60.
lead_paragraph: The Islamist militant group the Shabab said it carried out consecutive suicide bombings in the city of Baidoa that killed at least 20 people.

headline.main: Twin Suicide Bombings Kill at Least 20 as Shabab Violence Intensifies in Somalia
headline.print_headline: Twin Suicide Bombings Kill at Least 20 as Shabab Violence Intensifies in Somalia
